Many people question why I program.  They ask since I am not CS or ITM, why do I code.  Truthfully, why don't you?

If your future was created today, what would you do?  Because that is what I am doing.  I am creating my future and all I can see is  the need to have not only computer knowledge under my belt, but the next best thing.  Coding, propraming, all of that and the skills that come with it.  I didn't choose CS or ITM because I felt that it would limit me to only that, rather, I chose Communications.  This gives me a unique approach to thing
























































































































































































































































































